race.comment: Competitive. SHALHAVMUSIK (5) finished fifth two runs back at Murray Bridge then improved last time out to score by 1.1 lengths as public elect after being in the firing line on the bend over this track and trip. Likely to be there at the finish again. SIR LEAPALOT (4) is usually thereabouts but finds it hard to win. Did a good job last start to finish third at Oakbank. Peaking now and can break through. LAPILLI (6) lifted strongly to score two runs back then was prominent in the run last time before finishing fourth at Port Lincoln. Cherry-ripe now and there's no reason she can't bounce back into the winner's circle. BROOKLYN BABY (11) ran a better race last start to finish a close second here behind SHALHAVMUSIK, after leading. Gets in better this time and can turn the tables. PEPERONCINO (7) was too bad to be true last time in town and should find this easier. Don't dismiss.
